Question (text): Why are local variable names beginning with an underscore discouraged?
Answer_1: They are used to indicate a private variables of a class
Answer_3: They are used to indicate global variables
Answer_Explanation: As Python has no concept of private variables, leading underscores are used to indicate variables that must not be accessed from outside the class.

Question (text): Which one of these is floor division?
Answer_Explanation: When both of the operands are integer then python chops out the fraction part and gives you the round off value, to get the accurate answer use floor division. This is floor division. For ex, 5/2 = 2.5 but both of the operands are integer so answer of this expression in python is 2. To get the 2.5 answer, use floor division.

Question (text): What is the answer to this expression, 22%3 is?
Answer_Explanation: Modulus operator gives the remainder. So, 22%3 gives the remainder, that is, 1.
